revision.text:
The '''Centre International des Civilisations Bantu''' ('''CICIBA''') is a cultural organization based in [[Libreville]], [[Gabon]]. Established at the initiative of [[Heads of state of Gabon|Gabonese president]] [[Omar Bongo]] on January 8, 1983, it is dedicated to the study of the [[Bantu peoples]].
In 2012, it was announced that the center would be rehabilitated after its abandonment in 1988 for lack of funding.<ref>http://en.gabonews.com/headlines-reader-en/items/the-ciciba-soon-to-be-renovated.html{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
CICIBA's member nations include [[Angola]], Cameroon, [[Central African Republic]], [[Comoros]], [[Republic of the Congo]], [[Democratic Republic of Congo]], [[Equatorial Guinea]], Gabon, [[Rwanda]], [[São Tomé and Príncipe]], and [[Zambia]].{{cn|date=May 2018}}
